  "instructions": [
    "Heat 2 tablespoons of coconut oil in a deep frying pan over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the chopped garlic and sauté for 1 minute until fragrant.",
    "Add the diced potatoes and cook for 5-7 minutes until they start to brown.",
    "In a separate bowl, whisk together the hojicha, water, lemon juice, honey, and cornstarch until smooth.",
    "Add the mixture to the pan with the potatoes and stir to combine.",
    "Bring the mixture to a boil, then reduce the heat to medium-low and simmer for 5-7 minutes until the sauce has thickened.",
    "Season with salt and black pepper to taste.",
    "Serve the hojicha bowl hot, garnished with chopped cilantro, crushed almonds, and chopped dates."
